The paper discusses deep generative models for medical imaging, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of Bayesian reformulation for reasoning about model uncertainty, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses classification and semantic segmentation tasks, which are topics in natural language processing (cs.CL).
